---
// Story 2.3 — the custom not-found / broken-link state (AC4).
//
// Astro builds this to `dist/404.html`. `astro preview` (the Playwright harness)
// and Azure Static Web Apps both serve it for unmatched routes WITH a 404 HTTP
// status by default — so a dead `.md` link (rewritten to a would-be `/route`
// that no page emits) lands here as a clear "page not found" state, never a
// crash and never a soft-200 (which would be an SEO defect, FR-7/NFR-4).
//
// Rendered through the same `Page` layout as content pages, so it inherits the
// GitHub theme, the semantic <html lang> -> <head> -> <body> -> <main>/<article>
// shell, the single-<h1> discipline, and the JS-free contract. No site-header /
// pitch-card chrome (that is Story 2.6), no client JS.
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="Page not found">
  <h1>Page not found</h1>
  <p>
    We couldn&rsquo;t find that page. The markdown file it points to may have
    been moved, renamed, or never existed.
  </p>
  <p><a href="/">Go back home</a></p>
</Page>
